Lab 1 – Question 1: Twice the Square of an Integer

The objective of this experiment is to write a C program that calculates twice the square of integers between 0 and 511. The program uses a user-defined function to perform the calculation and stores the results in an array.


#include <stdio.h>          // Enables input/output functions such as printf

#define MAX 512             // Defines the range of numbers from 0 to 511

/*
   Function to calculate twice the square of a given integer
*/
int twiceSquare(int n)
{
    return 2 * n * n;       // Returns 2 multiplied by the square of n
}

int main()
{
    int result[MAX];        // Array to store results

    /*
      Compute twice the square of each number
      from 0 to 511 and store it in the array
    */
    for (int i = 0; i < MAX; i++)
    {
        result[i] = twiceSquare(i);
    }

    /*
      Display the first 10 results
      for verification purposes
    */
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
    {
        printf("2 * (%d^2) = %d\n", i, result[i]);
    }

    return 0;               // Program termination
}





